I"<p>many developers push their code to git repo with funny or sometimes silly comments (i do that sometimes) like this <a href="https://whatthecommit.com/">whatthecommit</a> site, but maybe it will be more hips (like hipsters do) if i can fetch last.fm api from current listened music and add them to my commit message.</p>

<p>here’s the idea</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">$ git commit -m "fixing some bugs $(last_fm)" </code></p>

<p>the last command is to insert my last.fm current track.
so if we browse the log it will be shown <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">"fixing some bugs while listening to U2 - Stay"</code>. if i don’t listened any track it will return <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">"with no music"</code> (or any other message).</p>

